# emergentintegrations — AI Agent Rules

## LLM calls: use emergentintegrations package only

NEVER use the raw OpenAI SDK directly.
NEVER set baseURL, defaultHeaders, or Authorization headers manually.
NEVER create wrapper functions like createLlmClient() or getAIClient().
NEVER write response.choices[0].message.content to unwrap responses.
NEVER add "openai" to package.json dependencies — it ships inside emergentintegrations already. Adding it directly causes version conflicts.

ALWAYS use:
```js
const { LlmChat, UserMessage } = require("emergentintegrations");
const chat = new LlmChat(process.env.EMERGENT_LLM_KEY, sessionId, systemMessage)
  .withModel("anthropic", "claude-sonnet-4-6");
const reply = await chat.sendMessage(new UserMessage({ text: input }));
```

LlmChat requires an Emergent API key (sk-emergent-*). A key that doesn't start
with sk-emergent- throws ChatError immediately at construction, not partway
through a request. Never pass a direct OpenAI, Anthropic, or Google key to
LlmChat. OpenAITextToSpeech, OpenAISpeechToText, and OpenAIImageGeneration are
different — they accept either an Emergent key or a direct OpenAI key.
No manual proxy configuration needed for LlmChat. Ever.


Module system: package supports BOTH CommonJS and ESM natively.
Check package.json — if "type": "module" use import syntax, otherwise require.
NEVER use createRequire as a workaround — native ESM imports work.
  CJS: const { LlmChat, UserMessage } = require("emergentintegrations");
  ESM: import { LlmChat, UserMessage } from "emergentintegrations";
All subpaths (/llm/utils, /llm/openai/textToSpeech, etc.) work in both.

Read AGENTS.md for full usage reference.
